<item>
            <title>[FELIX-722] Can&apos;t manage split packages with Require-Bundle header</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-722</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Attached to this post a sample code which tries to manage split packages with the&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;Require-Bundle&quot; header. &lt;br/&gt;
It does not work with felix 1.2.1 (but sounds like working with knoperfish).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please have a look at the following felix forum post:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mail-archive.com/users@felix.apache.org/msg02044.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.mail-archive.com/users@felix.apache.org/msg02044.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
